results.name: Number of primes p such that n divided by p leaves a 1 or a composite (nonzero) remainder.
example: a(7) = 2: there are 2 primes viz. 2,3 which leave a remainder 1 on dividing 7.
results.author: _Amarnath Murthy_, Aug 01 2002
